Menu zones.

A menu zone turns a patch of the map into a kiosk: the player stands inside it, presses the interact key, and a menu opens. Point it at the shop menu and you have a shop counter; point it at the settings menu and you have a control panel; point it at the weapons or items menu and you have a locker or a stash. It's how a map author wires the game's menus to physical places rather than leaving them all on global keystrokes.

How a menu zone works.

The zone covers a rectangular area. While the player is inside it, pressing the interact key opens the menu the zone was set to. The available menus are the following:

default — the map editor menu (add, edit, and remove lines; copy and paste raw map data; delete, load, reload, or start a new map).
build — the build catalog for placing entities.

settings — in-game preferences.
stats — the player's stats.

zones — the text-zone teleporter, for jumping to a named text zone.
info — the objects currently on the field.

weapons — the weapons inventory.
shields — the shields inventory.

character — the character themes.

items — the items inventory.
shop — spend points.

komlog — the kombat log.
pause — the pause menu.

On a compiled (shipped) map, a menu zone set to default does nothing but tell the player the map can't be edited, since compiled maps are read-only; the other menus work normally. This makes the default menu zone a handy author tool while building that quietly disables itself once the map ships.

Menu zone fields.

The menu zone form takes the following:

Coordinates. A minimum and maximum x and y (and a minimum and maximum z on 3d maps), marking the area the menu can be opened from.

Menu to open. Which of the menus listed above the zone opens.

Authoring menu zones by hand.

If you edit main.sif directly, a menu zone is: menu_zone minx maxx miny maxy menuname. On 3d maps a minimum and maximum z follow the y pair: menu_zone minx maxx miny maxy minz maxz menuname. The menu name is the short identifier for the menu — default, build, settings, stats, zones, info, weapons, shields, character, items, shop, komlog, or pause. A line with no menu name defaults to the map editor menu.
